parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning seat belt control module can cause the seat belt to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt is stuck
the seat belt will not retract
the seat belt unbuckles when pressure is applied
the automatic shoulder belt does not move back and forth.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A warped flywheel can cause the clutch release bearings to fail prematurely, leading to difficulty shifting gears, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Difficulty shifting gears
clutch failure
premature wear on clutch components.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Black Smoke Emission on Cold Start-up
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The emission of black smoke on cold start-up can indicate a problem with the engine's combustion process, potentially causing decreased fuel efficiency, increased emissions, and decreased engine performance.
symptoms: Black smoke emitted from the exhaust on cold start-up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the automatic transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or become stuck in gear, increasing the risk of accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission stops working while driving
the vehicle will not shift out of first gear
the vehicle will not shift into higher gears
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in the transmission can cause premature wear or failure, leading to unexpected transmission failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails unexpectedly
the transmission requires frequent repairs or rebuilding
the transmission exhibits unusual behavior or hesitation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water damage to the transmission can cause corrosion or electrical failure, leading to transmission failure, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails after exposure to water
the transmission will not shift out of first gear
the transmission will not shift into higher gears
the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaky fuel injectors can cause a fire hazard, as fuel can leak onto hot engine components, potentially igniting and causing a vehicle fire. Additionally, leaky injectors can lead to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Engine misfires
rough engine idle
decreased fuel efficiency
engine hesitation or stumbling
fuel odor or leak
engine warning light illumination.
